The leadership and members of the Federal Polytechnic Offa Alumni Association (FEDPOFFA), has congratulated the rector of the institution, Dr Ademola Abdulateef Olatunji, on his award as the Best Rector in Nigeria. In a congratulatory message signed by the National President of the association, Ayo Adeyemi, the association described the award as a well deserved one, just as the Rector was encouraged not to relent in raising the standards of the institution. “We congratulate and rejoice with the Rector and the entire Management for the well-deserved award and encourage him not to relent in his effort at making our citadel of learning a world-class institution that will be enviable to others,” the association said. ALSO READ: Ogun gov, Abiodun lures investors with business plan at UNGA Rotary Club distributes free exercise books to pupils in… Nigeria makes World Bank’s list for top-20 ‘improvers… Task Force raids Lagos brothel, nabs 14 suspects with… Nigerian governors storm New York for SDGs Olatunji was awarded as the Best Rector of the Nigerian polytechnics by the Senior Staff Association of Polytechnics in Nigeria during an event that took place at merit house, Abuja on Tuesday. The Alumni association, however, pledged its continued support to the school, just as it charged the Alumnus to always be a good ambassador of the institution. “We shall on our part continue to partner with the School’s Management in various areas that requires our intervention from time to time. “We are using this medium to charge our Alumnus to continue to be good ambassadors of the Polytechnic in every sphere of life they operate. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
